data.prayer: Father, knowing that teachers will be judged more strictly, help the local leaders in Västmanland, Sweden to be careful with their words.
data.verse: Not many of you should become teachers, my brothers, for you know that we who teach will be judged with greater strictness.

data.location_label: Photo from the state of Västmanland, Sweden
data.section_summary: What people or resources could you pray for in this photo?

data.prayer: Spirit, renew the call of John the Baptist in the state of Västmanland. Send out bold servants who will call all to repent.
data.verse: Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.

data.prayer: Father, you know every soul, and you know who are yours and who are yet to be yours out of the 256,200 people living in Västmanland, Sweden. Please, call your lost sheep to yourself.
data.verse: For I will take you out of the nations; I will gather you from all the countries and bring you back into your own land.

data.prayer: Lord, please provide elders whose hearts are completely yours in every town in the state of Västmanland.
data.verse: The reason I left you in Crete was that you might put in order what was left unfinished and appoint elders in every town, as I directed you.

data.prayer: Lord, bring the blind by a way that they don’t know. Lead the Tajik people in paths that they don’t know. Make darkness light before them and crooked places straight. Do not forsake the Tajik people.
Jesus, remind the disciples in the state of Västmanland to train each other to obey all that you commanded, and that you will be with them as they do it.
data.verse: and teaching them to obey everything I have commanded you. And surely I am with you always, to the very end of the age."

data.prayer: Spirit, encourage every believer in Västmanland, Sweden to do the work of an evangelist with their friends and neighbors.
data.verse: But you, keep your head in all situations, endure hardship, do the work of an evangelist

data.prayer: Over 44.14 percent of the people of Västmanland are far from Jesus.
